<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>depends on the 25s</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Tempra[CC]">Tempra[CC]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:35 a.m. 13/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> depends on the 25s<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=860" TARGET=_self>Re: A few suggestions for PvP</A> (Zariin)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>2 Wizards will NEVER eat any lvl 30 at this point in the game... the resistance of their spells is way to high for only 5 levels.. heck at one lvl higher my friend never hurt me once and that was when we were both in the 20's. They really need to make resist skill related and not level related.

<P>True...at levels after the late 20's to mid-late 30's one's
<BR>&gt; "Zone Peers" will likely outlevel others by the
<BR>&gt; "buffer." However, at this stage, there are no quick
<BR>&gt; kills, and also in these zones, there will likely be people on
<BR>&gt; the high side of the "buffer" of the attacker, but out
<BR>&gt; of range of the target. It all boils down to the fact that
<BR>&gt; everyone will eventually be a target if they do not keep
<BR>&gt; progressing.
<P>&gt; Two level 5's cannot take a single level 10, but 2 level 25's
<BR>&gt; will eat a level 30.
<P>&gt; I am excited to see the results play out for the sake of PvP.
<P>&gt; Zariin
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
